 Cartographer's Society library.
 As far as map collections went, theirs was without equal, and it was largely
 free for perusal as well – so long as you never destroyed anything, you only
 had to pay for maps you wanted the library to copy for you.
 Zorian had spent a few days there the last time he had visited the capital,
 just browsing the shelves for any map that caught his fancy, and swore he
 would visit again when he had the time.
 This seemed as good an excuse as any.

\end_layout

