 More accurately, he paid extra to have an instructor assigned to him for
 individual lessons, so he could save some time.
 Zorian was pleasantly surprised by the mage they sent him in response – the
 young man assigned to him was polite and straightforward in his teaching
 methods.
 A welcome reprieve from Zorian's usual luck with teachers.
 He only attended three sessions with the man, but that was enough to give him
 a plethora of mapping spells, not all of which dealt with classical paper
